Klikor IDE Bridge 2.0.0 is a ground-up rewrite of the idea-plugin/ module, built entirely on stable,
public IntelliJ Platform API (zero internal API usage -- no `.impl.` classes, no
`org.jetbrains.ide.RestService`, no reflection into IDE internals). It is no longer generated from an
upstream source checkout the way 1.x was; instead it independently re-implements the same local HTTP
action-execution protocol that intellij-streamdeck-plugin defined and that Klikor IDE Bridge 1.x served,
using JDK's own `com.sun.net.httpserver` (the same plain-JDK HTTP server approach that upstream's own
`RemoteActionServer.java` used, which 2.0.0's `BridgeServer.kt` is adapted from as a reference/template)
instead of upstream's platform-`impl`-classes executor. Attribution to JetBrains and the Apache-2.0 license
carries forward unchanged; see LICENSE.txt.

2.0.0 declares sinceBuild = 243 with no until-build (open-ended), and ships as a single Marketplace
artifact for all supported IDEs 2024.3 and newer -- replacing the three-version 1.0.0/1.1.0/1.2.0
build-range ladder described below, which is retained here for provenance/history.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Legacy versions (1.0.0 / 1.1.0 / 1.2.0) -- forked directly from upstream source
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Klikor IDE Bridge shipped a three-version marketplace ladder prior to 2.0.0, mirroring upstream's own
release channels (upstream verifier surfaced that upstream main HEAD references `ActionTreeGroupUtil`, a
class that only exists on IntelliJ Platform 262/2026.2 -- see per-version notes below):

Klikor IDE Bridge 1.0.0 was forked from commit db611224b3dce5a111cc8051e550fefa7ea7125e ("Release 2025.1
version", the last state of the idea-plugin module that declared sinceBuild = 243), idea-plugin/
subdirectory only. It was published on the JetBrains Marketplace capped to build range 243-251.*.

Klikor IDE Bridge 1.1.0 was built from upstream commit 9005402dd78415b99f45e5220c0cbaef075b063a ("Update
plugin to support 2026.1 and upgrade dependencies", 2026-03-26) -- upstream's own "2026.1" Marketplace
release commit (pluginVersion = 2026.1, pluginSinceBuild = 252 there). This predates upstream's
platform-262 compatibility fix (`git log -S ActionTreeGroupUtil` pins that reference to commit 5af9d10,
2026-05-14, well after 9005402), so this build's ActionsTree.java did not reference the 262-only API.
It declared sinceBuild = 252, untilBuild = 261.* and was published as the second Marketplace release
channel, so 243-251.* IDEs resolved to 1.0.0, 252-261.* IDEs resolved to 1.1.0, and 262+ IDEs resolved to
1.2.0.

Klikor IDE Bridge 1.2.0 re-synced the idea-plugin/ subdirectory to upstream main at commit
9487e193c331cd9b53e7d504f85c446c769bc0ff ("add claude code action", 2026-05-29), which carried upstream's
platform-262 compatibility fix (ActionTreeGroupUtil). It declared sinceBuild = 262 (no until-build) and
was published as the third Marketplace release channel, so 262+ IDEs resolved to 1.2.0.

All three legacy versions carried the identical Klikor rebrand (plugin id/name/vendor/description,
focus-gating default, and HTTP server log strings) applied identically at each version's upstream base
commit. dist/klikor-ide-bridge-1.1.0.zip is the built 1.1.0 plugin artifact, kept here for release/upload
convenience since its source (upstream commit 9005402) isn't checked into this working tree; 1.0.0's
source lives in this repo's git history (see the commit that first added `klikor-jetbrains-plugin/`).
Their approach is superseded by 2.0.0's independent, public-API-only implementation described above.

